						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulōttuṅga-chōḷadēva III: Year 25 = 1202-03 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription appears to record a gift of some <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp. The endowed material (money or sheep) is stated to have been received by Uḍaiyapiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Tiruchchiṟṟambala-bhaṭṭaṉ who had agreed to measure one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee.</p>						

